FBIS4-58416 "drnes086dd_94002" FBIS-NES-94-086 Daily Report 3 May 1994 Palestinian Affairs Oppositionists React to Signing of Self-Rule Accord Oppositionists React to Signing of Self-Rule Accord PFLP, DFLP Declare Day of Mourning JN0305180794 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1700 GMT 3 May 94 JN0305180794 Paris Radio Monte Carlo Arabic BFN [Excerpt] [passage omitted] The Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine [PFLP] and the Democratic Front for the Liberation of Palestine [DFLP] have declared tomorrow, Wednesday, a day of national mourning and have asked the people of the occupied West Bank and Gaza Strip to observe a general strike. In a statement distributed in the occupied territories today, the two fronts said that the implementation of the Gaza-Jericho agreement will constitute one of the most dangerous and difficult periods in the Palestinian people's struggle because complete coordination now exists between the Palestinian side and the occupation forces, as the statement put it. [passage omitted]
